snippet.textDisplay:
Hi my name is Wellington.

And I'm from Brazil.


I recently started translating videos of super interesting talk shows (like yours) where world-renowned stars are presented and interviewed.



I realized the need for this service when I activated the translation mode of Youtube itself to accompany one of these interviews and I was simply disappointed with the low quality of the translation ... in fact the translation in this configuration mode is, in most cases, unreadable, justifying the small audience of Brazilians in this type of international media (we are 200 million in habitants who do not speak English) so I had the idea of ​​translating as faithfully as possible, but adapting the contemporary inflections and personalisms, typical of each language and culture, that when printing them in another language, they deserve special attention and care so that nothing is lost in the interpretation of Brazilian viewers when they accompany their international celebrities.

Well, presenting my business; what I am proposing is for you to indicate the videos that you would like to translate on your channel, preserving your original spirit, but with careful care to adapt to Brazilian Portuguese using the You tube itself, to the point that these same videos become understandable by Brazilian public and with that they start to have the proper scale of consumption, since today, Brazil has an audience of more than 180,000,000 internet users in search of interesting things but above all; understandable.

If you are interested this is my address for questions and requests wellingtonrwa@@t
Congratulations on your excellent work and thank you for the opportunity.
